---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Mastering CSS Grid Architectures | Balaji Blogs" description="A deep dive into advanced CSS Grid techniques for building complex, responsive web layouts.">
  <article class="animate-in">
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>Mastering CSS Grid Architectures</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">Published on April 18, 2026 &bull; 6 min read</div>
    </header>

    <div class="article-content">
      <p>CSS Grid completely revolutionized how developers approach layout on the web. By offering a two-dimensional grid system, it handles complex alignments that would have required multiple wrapper divs and chaotic floats.</p>

      <h2>Thinking in Two Dimensions</h2>
      <p>Unlike Flexbox, which excels at one-dimensional alignment (either rows or columns), Grid is built for structure. You can define areas like headers, main content, sidebars, and footers with just a few lines of visually intuitive CSS code.</p>

      <h2>The Power of auto-fit</h2>
      <p>One of the true magic tricks of Grid is the <code>repeat(auto-fit, minmax())</code> function. It enables fully responsive grid layouts without a single media query. As the browser window expands, new columns form automatically based on your defined minimum width constraints.</p>

      <p>Embracing Grid syntax natively means you can start reducing reliance on robust styling frameworks, cutting down bundle sizes while maintaining perfect pixel control over your application UI.</p>
    </div>

    <a href="/blog" class="back-link">&larr; Back to all articles</a>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .article-meta {
    color: var(--muted-text);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .article-content {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 3rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
  }

  .article-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .article-content h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-color);
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-color);
  }
</style>
